OL,3,CHow quickly are seasons warming in the
OL,4,CUK and what impact is this having?
OL,6,FAround 90% of the additional heat
OL,7,Fwe've added has been absorbed by the
OL,8,Focean, and in recent years we've seen
OL,9,Frecord warm sea surface temperatures,
OL,10,Fwhich have a major impact on sea life
OL,11,F(i.e. corals) and ocean circulation.
OL,13,FOur weather becomes 'bigger' as a
OL,14,Fresult of warmer sea temperatures too;
OL,15,FClimate Central analysis found that
OL,16,FStorm Eowyn, which brought record-
OL,17,Fbreaking gusts of wind, intensified
OL,18,Fover unusually warm sea temperatures.
